                            <comment id="289768" author="adilger" created="Tue, 19 Jan 2021 04:56:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on master &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/993b91cb-ed0a-47fe-ab06-a768b65f43ff&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/993b91cb-ed0a-47fe-ab06-a768b65f43ff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="232844" author="adilger" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2018 07:41:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;According to &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/show_bug.cgi?id=12622&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;b=12622&lt;/a&gt; this test has been intermittently failing since Lustre 1.4, so it should not be considered an error if the object creation is uneven.  This will likely need changes to the object allocator, like &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9&quot; title=&quot;Optimize weighted QOS Round-Robin allocator&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9&quot;&gt;LU-9&lt;/a&gt;, to keep it more balanced over time.  In the meantime, it should be added to the &lt;tt&gt;ALWAYS_EXCEPT&lt;/tt&gt; list again or use &lt;tt&gt;error_ignore&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
